  <title>Introduction to Cybersecurity</title>
  <offered>fall</offered>

  <scheduleType>lecture</scheduleType>
  <catalogDescription>This course covers the fundamental issues and principles of computer-and-network security by studying the theories and practicing through hands-on assignments and lab exercises. The course will look at the capabilities of modern cryptographic systems and the NIST Cybersecurity Framework. Students will learn how to secure a computer, or a network, by first decomposing its security requirement into components and applying common techniques to enforce each security component. Mathematical backgrounds of well-known security algorithms will also be discussed in this course.</catalogDescription>
